comment:
I can't speak for everyone but I can share my opinion. To me I can tell Amber is lieing about her abuse is bc I went through a horrible relationship of DV. So bad I have permanent injuries. It's been about 12 yrs since I left it. While I was being abused I lied and said I was not being abused. 2 reasons why... 1 being that an abuser will be even more abusive if they find out you said anything to anyone. 2 because I was personally humiliated.
I could not talk about my abuse for yrs. I can say I was abused now after all this time but I still cannot go into the details. Most of my feelings of humiliation are bc I considered myself a strong person who could never of been abused, but yet it happened. And the other being I hate always hearing "Why did you stay? I would never let a person do that to me."
I have even heard those words from loved ones who know what happened. But in summary it's not a subject you talk about easily. So I find when people yell it from the rooftops to anyone and everyone that I have a tendency not to believe them. Please don't hate on me I've been through yrs of DV support groups and most women there had a hard time saying "I was abused".
I'm not saying it's that way for everyone but it's my personal experience.

comment: This is the reason I have never ever supported the MeToo movement,   As a woman, it disgusts me that we keep telling society that when a woman comes forward with allegations, we should just believe her with no proof.  I am sorry, but I cannot do that.  I don't care if you're a man or a woman, there needs to be proof.  We cannot just ruin people's lives because of hearsay.   I have known many many women in my lifetime that have lied about men because they were angry and bitter.   I know some experts say that it is a very small percentage that lie about abuse, rape, etc.  but I don't think so, I believe it's a lot more than we know.  I also am very upset that when these women get caught lying, they don't face the same punishment as the man.   If you lied and ruined someone's life, then at the very least, you should get the same punishment if not worse.  I think what we fail to realize is how many people actually do lie about stuff like this.  When a woman is mad, bitter, jealous, etc., she is capable of anything.  I have known a couple of women in college who lied about rape all because the guy broke up with them and started dating someone else.  I have also known women who have lied about being pregnant just to keep a man.  I find that pathetic and disgusting.   Let's start making it equal.  Whether you're a man or a woman and if you have ruined someone's life because of lies, then you should be prosecuted to the full extent of the law.    I also forgot to mention how lies like these make it harder for real victims of abuse and rape.   I also think we need to ban together and start holding the media accountable for not reporting the truth, not fact-checking stories and not reporting once the lies come out because it doesn't fit their narrative.   Anyway, that's my rant.  Thanks for reading.
